Show HN: What's today's date if we used a perrenial calendar
text:
I was thinking about a decimal clock as totally normal people sometimes do and eventually ended up doing some research about a decimal calendar (which might sound appealing at first, but ends up being very impractical) and came across other calendar proposals.

I wondered what dates today, my birthday, and holidays would be on those calendars and how one would find that information. I looked for websites that did what Better calendars does, but couldn't find any that I found appealing so I decided to build it myself.

Ask HN: REST Custom Method: vs. /
text:
Please help me understand why we would want to do this. At work, we've adopted this guide to specify an action on a resource:

https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/custom_methods

Instead of /api/job/:foo/cancel, they use /api/job/:foo:cancel.

I imagine URL parsers and routers have a much easier time with the former compared to the later. In the later, I imagine most people are having to do additional tokenizing to enable further routing. I can't think of a redeeming factor.

Thanks
